    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.77/127.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1369.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith without
                    comment and for the information of the Department or such other Departments as
                    may be interested therein a copy of a letter from Mr. T. K. Eccles and <pb
                        facs="1038" n="922" xml:id="pg_922"/> Mr. J. F. Ealy, representatives
                    respectively of the Order of Railway Conductors and of the Brotherhood of
                    Locomotive Engineers.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Representatives of the Railway
                                Men</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico, D. F.</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1912</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: For your information will state that
                        to-morrow something over 600 engineers and conductors will leave the service
                        of the National Railways of Mexico. It will be a part of the duty of the
                        undersigned to know where these men have located. If their services should
                        be needed by our country in handling troop trains in the Republic of Mexico
                        we will be able to furnish all the men needed and these men will thoroughly
                        know the track they are to run over.</p>
                    <p>A wire or letter to T. K. Eccles, Alberta Hotel, El Paso, Texas, will be all
                        that is needed.</p>
                    <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">T. K. Eccles</hi>.</item>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. F. Ealy.</hi>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
